WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.200
AhaSlides has two language settings — one for the presenter interface, one for the audience.

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:09.030
Click the globe icon in the header to open the presenter language list.

00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:18.700
Choose from 27 interface languages — English, Español, Français, Deutsch, 中文, 日本語 and more. The interface switches instantly.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:22.890
Now let's set the audience language. It lives inside each presentation's Settings.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:27.730
After opening a presentation, click Poll to add a slide — then we'll go to Settings.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.940
Click the Settings icon in the right panel to open presentation settings.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.180
In the Settings panel, click Presentation language to reach the audience language picker.

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:46.840
AhaSlides supports 32 audience languages. English is selected by default. Scroll through Bahasa Indonesia, Čeština, Deutsch, Español, Français, and 27 more.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:51.490
Let's choose Español. All participant-facing text switches to Spanish immediately.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:55.500
The language is saved automatically. Close Settings to return to the editor.

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:57.960
Click Preview to see the audience view in Spanish.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:03.620
The participant screen switches to Spanish — the join text, buttons, and interface all appear in Español.

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:08.190
Both settings save automatically. Combine them to run fully multilingual sessions.
